comments: This course was fantastic - I would highly recommend this course to any PhD student, or anyone interested in data analysis, management and presentation. Prior to this course I had no experience of coding and was anxious about the level of difficulty. Sam and the team made the content very accessible and enjoyable, and everyone was approachable and friendly.

Could we probably have another course on statistics? something similar to this course in structure. i have a basic understanding of statistics and think such a course would be really helpful for my research.
very helpful and knowledgeable staff. thanks
Thanks so much, it was a fantastic course. I even think I would take it again.
Great course for individuals not have any experience of R like me. It is not as difficult as I originally thought. I very much appreciate the opportunity!

It would be nice to have this course for slightly more extended time - meaning within 3 days it is not easy to catch up everything. However, because of the help of our extremely helpful instructors it was much easier at least to understand something. Thank you very much Sam, Nicolas, Faheem. I personally didn't attend Day 1 cause I didn't receive confirmation email so I thought it was fully booked. But all instructors and especially Faheem helped me a lot to catch up with Day 1 asd Day 2 within only 1 day. Therefore lots of thanks. I appreciate your guys effort. We definitely need this course to be repeated next Term.
Need to arrange an feedback workshop for one day

A step by step process of manipulating R would have made the course very easy to learn. The organisation of the course would have started from appreciating R interface to importing/exporting data, stepwise programming for statistical analysis.

intro_content/topics_not_convered: For an introductory course, the content is perfect
comments: good content and the instructors were extremely helpful.
